# Lab 6A – Create Custom systemd Service

1. Create working directory
   mkdir -p /opt/mylab

2. Create script
   vi /opt/mylab/daemon-workload.sh

3. Add script content and save

4. Make script executable
   chmod +x /opt/mylab/daemon-workload.sh

5. Create environment file
   vi /etc/sysconfig/daemon-workload

6. Add configuration
   INTERVAL=10

7. Create systemd unit file
   vi /etc/systemd/system/daemon-workload.service

8. Reload systemd
   systemctl daemon-reexec
   systemctl daemon-reload

9. Enable and start service
   systemctl enable --now daemon-workload.service

10. Verify service status
    systemctl status daemon-workload.service
